# Brand assets (`public/`)

General **`next/image`** policy, **`localPatterns` / `remotePatterns`**, and SVG defaults: `.cursor/rules/images.mdc`.

Authoritative paths live in [`lib/site.ts`](lib/site.ts) (`FAVICON_ICO`, `APP_ICON_*`, `BRAND_*`, `DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE`). **Browser tab:** [`app/layout.tsx`](app/layout.tsx) `metadata.icons` + `shortcut` with `media: "(prefers-color-scheme: light|dark)"` (not `next-themes`). **`/favicon.ico`** is a real ICO in `public/` (regenerate via `pnpm icons:favicon` from `APP_ICON_512_PNG` source). Avoid **`app/icon.png`** if it would override themed `<link rel="icon">` entries. Prefer importing constants instead of string literals.

## Taxonomy

- **Symbol / app mark** (`APP_ICON_*`, maskable variant): tab icon via `metadata.icons` — **transparent** `APP_ICON_192/512_PNG` for both `prefers-color-scheme` values; PWA manifest adds `APP_ICON_MASKABLE_512_PNG` with `purpose: "maskable"`; Apple touch icon; in-app [`AfendaBrandIcon`](components/afenda-brand.tsx) uses **transparent** `APP_ICON_512_PNG` for both themes (no maskable swap); default OG/Twitter (`DEFAULT_OG_IMAGE`).
- **Combined lockup** (`BRAND_COMBINED_LOCKUP_PNG` light, `BRAND_COMBINED_LOCKUP_DARK_PNG` for `html.dark`): [`AfendaBrandLockup`](components/afenda-brand.tsx) (`"use client"`) on marketing/auth flows, **dashboard** shell header, **account** / **admin** layouts, `not-found` / `error` / root `loading` where brand presence matters. Dark raster is keyed from `brand-guideline/dark-full-icon-bar.png` via [`scripts/knockout-dark-lockup-bg.mjs`](scripts/knockout-dark-lockup-bg.mjs); output `dark-full-icon-bar-transparent.png`.
- **Typography / wordmark** (`BRAND_TYPOGRAPHY_LOCKUP_SVG`, `BRAND_WORDMARK_MONO_SVG`): text-first branding; respect theme and contrast (semantic Tailwind surfaces — avoid hardcoded colors that fight tokens).
- **Maskable** (`APP_ICON_MASKABLE_512_PNG`): only for manifest entries with `purpose: "maskable"`; do not swap in arbitrary art without safe-zone awareness.

## UI (Next.js App Router)

- Use **`next/image`** for PNG marks; set **`width`**, **`height`**, and meaningful **`alt`** (e.g. site name or “Afenda logo”) per [Next.js images](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/getting-started/images).
- **`src` must match [`next.config.ts`](next.config.ts) `images.localPatterns`** (`/icons/**`, `/afenda-brand/**`). Other `public/` paths will return **400** from `/_next/image` until you extend the allowlist (and `#lib/site` if brand-related).
- **SVG** lockups: `next/image` with root-relative `src` is fine; SVG is served **unoptimized** by default (security). Do **not** enable `images.dangerouslyAllowSVG` in `next.config` for routine brand usage.
- Do not substitute **Lucide or generic icons** for product identity surfaces (nav brand, auth header).
- **Composition:** prefer small components (`BrandMark` / `BrandLockup` or layout wrappers with `children`) over one logo component with many boolean modes.

## Metadata and sharing

- Keep **`metadataBase`** and relative URLs consistent with [`app/layout.tsx`](app/layout.tsx). For `openGraph.images`, set **`width`**, **`height`**, and **`alt`** to match the asset.
- **`metadata.icons`:** use typed `url` / `sizes` / `type`. For light/dark-specific marks, use multiple `icon` entries with `media` (e.g. `prefers-color-scheme: dark`) per [generateMetadata](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/functions/generate-metadata).
- **PWA:** keep using [`app/manifest.ts`](app/manifest.ts) with `purpose: "any"` vs `"maskable"` as appropriate.

## Optional patterns (not default here)

- File-based **`opengraph-image`** or **`app/icon.tsx`** / **`app/icon.png`** — only if product needs a single generated/static tab asset; today themed tabs use **`metadata.icons`** + `media` instead.

## Process

- New files under `public/afenda-brand/` or `public/icons/` require updating [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md) (Brand assets / Images), this rule, [`lib/site.ts`](lib/site.ts) constants, [`app/layout.tsx`](app/layout.tsx) **`metadata.icons`** when tab art changes, run **`pnpm icons:favicon`** when the 512 source changes, and [`next.config.ts`](next.config.ts) **`localPatterns`** as needed (see **`.cursor/rules/images.mdc`**).
- The full Figma guideline raster (`afenda-figma-export-full-guideline.png`) is **gitignored** (GitHub 100 MB limit); keep it locally under `public/afenda-brand/brand-guideline/` for design reference.

## When unsure

Re-query **Context7** `/vercel/next.js` pinned to the repo’s Next major (see `AGENTS.md` toolchain) or **Vercel MCP** `search_vercel_documentation` for image optimization — do not rely on stale model knowledge.
